For the lessor, the asset being leased is accounted for as an asset and is depreciated as such.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ClaimsOutstanding
member.summary: Amounts owing to policy holders who have filed claims but have not yet been settled or paid.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LongTermContracts
member.summary: A supply contract in the physical market covering energy deliveries of more than 18 months, accounted for as part of Inventories.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.RealEstate
member.summary: Land and buildings which are held as inventory, normally by real estate companies or income trusts.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.PaymentofBills
member.summary: A bill or invoice is a document requesting payment for an order previously supplied.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LiabilitiesHeldforSaleCurrent
member.summary: Liabilities due within the next 12 months related from an asset classified as Held for Sale.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LiabilitiesHeldforSaleNonCurrent
member.summary: Liabilities related to an asset classified as held for sale excluding the portion due the next 12 months or operating cycle.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.UnclassifiedCurrentAssets
member.summary: Other current assets owned by the company that cannot be identified by other specific items in the Current Assets section.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DebtSecurities
member.summary: Debt securities held as investments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TotalFinancialLeaseObligations
member.summary: Represents the total amount of long-term capital leases that must be paid within the next accounting period for a Non- Differentiated Balance Sheet. Capital lease obligations are contractual obligations that arise from obtaining the use of property or equipment via a capital lease contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AccruedandDeferredIncomeCurrent
member.summary: Sum of Accrued Liabilities and Deferred Income (amount received in advance but the services are not provided in respect of amount) due within 1 year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AccruedandDeferredIncomeNonCurrent
member.summary: Sum of Accrued Liabilities and Deferred Income (amount received in advance but the services are not provided in respect of amount) due after 1 year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinanceLeaseReceivablesCurrent
member.summary: Accounts owed to the bank in relation to capital leases to be received within the next accounting period. Capital/ finance lease obligations are contractual obligations that arise from obtaining the use of property or equipment via a capital lease contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinanceLeaseReceivablesNonCurrent
member.summary: Accounts owed to the bank in relation to capital leases to be received beyond the next accounting period. Capital/ finance lease obligations are contractual obligations that arise from obtaining the use of property or equipment via a capital lease contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialLiabilitiesCurrent
member.summary: Financial related liabilities due within one year, including short term and current portions of long-term debt, capital leases and derivative liabilities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialLiabilitiesNonCurrent
member.summary: Financial related liabilities due beyond one year, including long term debt, capital leases and derivative liabilities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialAssetsDesignatedasFairValueThroughProfitorLossTotal
member.summary: Financial assets that are held at fair value through profit or loss comprise assets held for trading and those financial assets designated as being held at fair value through profit or loss.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TaxesAssetsCurrent
member.summary: Carrying amount due within one year of the balance sheet date (or one operating cycle, if longer) from tax authorities as of the balance sheet date representing refunds of overpayments or recoveries based on agreed-upon resolutions of disputes, and current deferred tax assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.OtherEquityInterest
member.summary: Other equity instruments issued by the company that cannot be identified by other specific items in the Equity section.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InterestBearingBorrowingsNonCurrent
member.summary: Carrying amount of any interest-bearing loan which is due after one year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.NonInterestBearingBorrowingsNonCurrent
member.summary: Non-interest bearing borrowings due after a year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TradeandOtherPayablesNonCurrent
member.summary: Sum of all non-current payables and accrued expenses.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InterestBearingBorrowingsCurrent
member.summary: Carrying amount of any interest-bearing loan.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.NonInterestBearingBorrowingsCurrent
member.summary: Non-interest bearing deposits in other financial institutions for short periods of time, usually less than 12 months.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.PensionandOtherPostRetirementBenefitPlansCurrent
member.summary: Total of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for obligations related to services received from employees, such as accrued salaries and bonuses, payroll taxes and fringe benefits.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.CashandBalanceswithCentralBanks
member.summary: The sum of cash and cash equivalents plus Federal Funds Sold. Including cash, petty cash/revolving funds/demand deposits with central banks and other kinds of accounts that have the general characteristics of demand deposits.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.PlacementwithBanksandOtherFinancialInstitutions
member.summary: Deposit accounts and placements that are deposited in a bank or other financial institution.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.OtherLoanAssets
member.summary: Reflects the carrying amount of any other unpaid loans, an asset of the bank.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingAssetsTotal
member.summary: An investment that is used to reduce the risk of adverse price movements in an asset, in a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet. Normally, a hedge consists of taking an offsetting position in a related security, such as a futures contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AssetsPledgedasCollateralSubjecttoSaleorRepledgingTotal
member.summary: Total value collateral assets pledged to the bank that can be sold or used as collateral for other loans.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TaxAssetsTotal
member.summary: Sum of total tax assets in a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet, includes Tax Receivables and Deferred Tax Assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AdvancesfromCentralBanks
member.summary: Borrowings from the central bank, which are primarily used to cover shortages in the required reserve balance and liquidity shortages.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.CertificatesofDepositsandOtherDebtSecuritiesIssued
member.summary: The carrying value as of the balance sheet date of all interest bearing promissory notes and certificates issued by a financial institution.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DepositCertificates
member.summary: A savings certificate entitling the bearer to receive interest. A CD bears a maturity date, a specified fixed interest rate and can be issued in any denomination.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DebenturesandDebtCertificates
member.summary: Instruments that are not secured by any collateral and are backed only by the creditworthiness and reputation of the financial institution. Debentures and debt certificates usually have terms last longer than a year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InterestBearingBorrowingsTotal
member.summary: Carrying amount of total borrowings on which enterprise paid the interest; on a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.NonInterestBearingBorrowingsTotal
member.summary: Non-interest bearing deposits in other financial institutions for relatively short periods of time; on a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.OtherBorrowedFunds
member.summary: Other borrowings by the bank to fund its activities that cannot be identified by other specific items in the Liabilities section.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialLiabilitiesDesignatedasFairValueThroughProfitorLossTotal
member.summary: Financial liabilities that are held at fair value through profit or loss.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialLiabilitiesMeasuredatAmortizedCostTotal
member.summary: Financial liabilities carried at amortized cost.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LoanCapital
member.summary: Subordinated loan capital to be repaid at a later date on a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingLiabilitiesTotal
member.summary: A liability derived from hedging instruments on a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LiabilitiesRecognizedforFairValueChangesinPortfolioHedgeofInterestRateRisk
member.summary: Liabilities recognized on hedge.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AccruedLiabilitiesTotal
member.summary: Liabilities which have occurred, but have not been paid or logged under accounts payable during an accounting period. In other words, obligations for goods and services provided to a company for which invoices have not yet been received; on a Non- Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DeferredIncomeTotal
member.summary: Collections of cash or other assets related to revenue producing activity for which revenue has not yet been recognized on a Non- Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DeferredTaxLiabilitiesTotal
member.summary: A future tax liability, resulting from temporary differences between book (accounting) value of assets and liabilities and their tax value or timing differences between the recognition of gains and losses in financial statements, on a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ReinsuranceAssets
member.summary: Reinsurance asset is insurance that is purchased by an insurance company from another insurance company.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ReinsuranceShareofInsuranceContract
member.summary: Accumulated share of insurance contract of reinsurance.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ReinsuranceShareofAccruedPolicyholderClaims
member.summary: Accrued claims with reinsurance companies.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DepositsMadeunderAssumedReinsuranceContract
member.summary: Deposits made under reinsurance.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsuranceContractAssets
member.summary: A contract under which one party (the insurer) accepts significant insurance risk from another party (the policyholder) by agreeing to compensate the policyholder if a specified uncertain future event (the insured event) adversely affects the policyholder. This includes Insurance Receivables and Premiums Receivables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsuranceReceivables
member.summary: Receivables from policyholders, agencies, and other operating parties in insurance companies, but excludes receivables from reinsurers.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsuranceContractLiabilities
member.summary: Any type of insurance policy that protects an individual or business from the risk that they may be sued and held legally liable for something such as malpractice, injury or negligence. Liability insurance policies cover both legal costs and any legal payouts for which the insured would be responsible if found legally liable. Intentional damage and contractual liabilities are typically not covered in these types of policies.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsurancePayables
member.summary: The carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of the known and estimated amounts owed to parties under insurance policies or other arrangements.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DepositsReceivedunderCededInsuranceContract
member.summary: Deposit received through ceded insurance contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InvestmentContractLiabilities
member.summary: Liabilities due on the insurance investment contract.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ConstructionGrants
member.summary: Government grants awarded to the company for its construction projects. They are capitalized by the company as part of the Property, Plant and Equipment.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DeferredCostCurrent
member.summary: Payments that will be assigned as expenses with one accounting period, but that are paid in advance and temporarily set up as current assets on the balance sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.PensionAndOtherPostretirementBenefitPlansTotal
member.summary: Total of the carrying values as of the balance sheet date of obligations incurred through that date and payable for obligations related to services received from employees, such as accrued salaries and bonuses, payroll taxes and fringe benefits. Used to reflect the current portion of the liabilities (due within one year or within the normal operating cycle if longer).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LiabilitiesHeldforSaleTotal
member.summary: Liabilities related to an asset classified as held for sale.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingAssetsNonCurrent
member.summary: An asset that is used to reduce the risk of adverse price movements in another asset.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingAssetsCurrent
member.summary: A security transaction which expires within a 12 month period that reduces the risk on an existing investment position.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ConvertibleLoansTotal
member.summary: Loans that entitles the lender (or the holder of loan debenture) to convert the loan to common or preferred stock (ordinary or preference shares) at a specified rate conversion rate and a specified time frame; in a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.BankLoansTotal
member.summary: Total debt financing obligation issued by a bank or similar financial institution to a company that entitles the lender or holder of the instrument to interest payments and the repayment of principal at a specified time; in a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.OtherLoansTotal
member.summary: Total other loans between the customer and bank which cannot be identified by other specific items in the Debt section; in a Non- Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingLiabilitiesNonCurrent
member.summary: A liability derived from hedging instruments. The amount due is outside of the next 12 months or operating cycle.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.HedgingLiabilitiesCurrent
member.summary: A liability derived from hedging instruments. The amount is due within the next 12 months or operating cycle.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsuranceFundsNonCurrent
member.summary: Liabilities related to insurance funds that are dissolved after one year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.InsuranceFundsCurrent
member.summary: Liabilities related to insurance funds that are dissolved within the year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DebtTotal
member.summary: The total aggregate of all written promises and/or agreements to repay a stated amount of borrowed funds at a specified date in the future; in a Non-Differentiated Balance Sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ComTreShaNum
member.summary: The treasury stock number of common shares. This represents the number of common shares owned by the company as a result of share repurchase programs or donations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.PreTreShaNum
member.summary: The treasury stock number of preferred shares. This represents the number of preferred shares owned by the company as a result of share repurchase programs or donations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.NetDebt
member.summary: This is a metric that shows a company's overall debt situation by netting the value of a company's liabilities and debts with its cash and other similar liquid assets. It is calculated using [Current Debt] + [Long Term Debt] - [Cash and Cash Equivalents].

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ShareIssued
member.summary: The number of authorized shares that is sold to and held by the shareholders of a company, regardless of whether they are insiders, institutional investors or the general public. Unlike shares that are held as treasury stock, shares that have been retired are not included in this figure. The amount of issued shares can be all or part of the total amount of authorized shares of a corporation.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AssetsHeldForSaleCurrent
member.summary: Short term assets set apart for sale to liquidate in the future and are measured at the lower of carrying amount and fair value less costs to sell.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.AssetsHeldForSaleNonCurrent
member.summary: Long term assets set apart for sale to liquidate in the future and are measured at the lower of carrying amount and fair value less costs to sell.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.BiologicalAssets
member.summary: Biological assets include plants and animals.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.CashRestrictedOrPledged
member.summary: Cash that the company can use only for specific purposes or cash deposit or placing of owned property by a debtor (the pledger) to a creditor (the pledgee) as a security for a loan or obligation.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.ConvertibleLoansNonCurrent
member.summary: A long term loan with a warrant attached that gives the debt holder the option to exchange all or a portion of the loan principal for an equity position in the company at a predetermined rate of conversion within a specified period of time.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.FinancialOrDerivativeInvestmentCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: Financial instruments that are linked to a specific financial instrument or indicator or commodity, and through which specific financial risks can be traded in financial markets in their own right, such as financial options, futures, forwards, etc.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.LoanAndLoanReceivables
member.summary: An asset account in a bank's general ledger that indicates the amounts owed by borrowers to the bank as of a given date.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.OtherInvestments
member.summary: Investments that are neither Investment in Financial Assets nor Long term equity investment, not expected to be cashed within a year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TradeAndOtherReceivablesNonCurrent
member.summary: Amounts due from customers or clients, more than one year from the balance sheet date, for goods or services that have been delivered or sold in the normal course of business, or other receivables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.BSFileDate
member.summary: Filing date of the Balance Sheet

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.DueFromRelatedParties
member.summary: For an unclassified balance sheet, carrying amount as of the balance sheet date of obligations due all related parties.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.TrustPreferredSecurities
member.summary: Preferred security issued by a trust created by the company, that is treated as a long-term liability.

member.name: M:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.#ctor
member.summary: Creates an instance of the BalanceSheet class

member.name: M:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet.UpdateValues(QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.BalanceSheet)
member.summary: Sets values for non existing periods from a previous instance
member.remarks: Used to fill-forward values from previous dates
member.param: The previous instance

member.name: T:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement
member.summary: Definition of the CashFlowStatement class

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.Amortization
member.summary: The systematic and rational apportionment of the acquisition cost of intangible operational assets to future periods in which the benefits contribute to revenue. This field is to include Amortization and any variation where Amortization is the first account listed in the line item, excluding Amortization of Intangibles.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CallsMaturitiesOfMaturitySecurities
member.summary: The aggregate amount of cash flow from securities calls, maturities, and redemption.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CapitalExpenditure
member.summary: Funds used by a company to acquire or upgrade physical assets such as property, industrial buildings or equipment. This type of outlay is made by companies to maintain or increase the scope of their operations. Capital expenditures are generally depreciated or depleted over their useful life, as distinguished from repairs, which are subtracted from the income of the current year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetCapitalExpenditureDisposals
member.summary: Funds used to (collect from) acquire or upgrade (disposal) physical assets such as property, industrial buildings or equipment. Refers to only those transactions which are specifically a capital expenditure or disposal.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashDividendsPaid
member.summary: Payments for the cash dividends declared by an entity to shareholders during the period. This element includes paid and unpaid dividends declared during the period for both common and preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFlowFromContinuingFinancingActivities
member.summary: Cash generated by or used in financing activities of continuing operations; excludes cash flows from discontinued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFlowFromContinuingInvestingActivities
member.summary: Cash generated by or used in investing activities of continuing operations; excludes cash flows from discontinued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFlowFromContinuingOperatingActivities
member.summary: Cash generated by or used in operating activities of continuing operations; excludes cash flows from discontinued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFlowFromDiscontinuedOperation
member.summary: The aggregate amount of cash flow from discontinued operation, including operating activities, investing activities, and financing activities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.FinancingCashFlow
member.summary: The net cash inflow (outflow) from financing activity for the period, which involve changes to the long-term liabilities and stockholders' equity.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.InvestingCashFlow
member.summary: An item on the cash flow statement that reports the aggregate change in a company's cash position resulting from any gains (or losses) from investments in the financial markets and operating subsidiaries, and changes resulting from amounts spent on investments in capital assets such as plant and equipment.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.OperatingCashFlow
member.summary: The net cash from (used in) all of the entity's operating activities, including those of discontinued operations, of the reporting entity. Operating activities include all transactions and events that are not defined as investing or financing activities. Operating activities generally involve producing and delivering goods and providing services. Cash flows from operating activities are generally the cash effects of transactions and other events that enter into the determination of net income.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.BeginningCashPosition
member.summary: The cash and equivalents balance at the beginning of the accounting period, as indicated on the Cash Flow statement.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.EndCashPosition
member.summary: The cash and cash equivalents balance at the end of the accounting period, as indicated on the Cash Flow statement. It is equal to the Beginning Cash and Equivalents, plus the Net Change in Cash and Equivalents.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedFinancing
member.summary: Cash generated by or used in financing activities of discontinued operations; excludes cash flows from continued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedFinancingActivities
member.summary: Cash generated by or used in financing activities of discontinued operations; excludes cash flows from continued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedInvesting
member.summary: The net cash inflow (outflow) from discontinued investing activities over the designated time period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedInvestingActivities
member.summary: The net cash inflow (outflow) from discontinued investing activities over the designated time period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedOperating
member.summary: The net cash from (used in) all of the entity's discontinued operating activities, excluding those of continued operations, of the reporting entity.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInAccountPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the account payables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInTaxPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the tax payables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInAccruedExpense
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the accrued expenses.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInAccruedInvestmentIncome
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period in investment income that has been earned but not yet received in cash.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangesInCash
member.summary: The net change between the beginning and ending balance of cash and cash equivalents.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInDeferredAcquisitionCosts
member.summary: The change of the unamortized portion as of the balance sheet date of capitalized costs that vary with and are primarily related to the acquisition of new and renewal insurance contracts.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInFederalFundsAndSecuritiesSoldForRepurchase
member.summary: The amount shown on the books that a bank with insufficient reserves borrows, at the federal funds rate, from another bank to meet its reserve requirements and the amount of securities that an institution sells and agrees to repurchase at a specified date for a specified price, net of any reductions or offsets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInFundsWithheld
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period associated with funds withheld.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInIncomeTaxPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the income tax payables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInInterestPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the interest payable. Interest payable means carrying value as of the balance sheet date of interest payable on all forms of debt.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInInventory
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the Inventories. Inventories represent merchandise bought for resale and supplies and raw materials purchased for use in revenue producing operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInLoans
member.summary: The net change that a lender gives money or property to a borrower and the borrower agrees to return the property or repay the borrowed money, along with interest, at a predetermined date in the future.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInLossAndLossAdjustmentExpenseReserves
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period in the reserve account established to account for expected but unspecified losses.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the payables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInPayablesAndAccruedExpense
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the payables and accrued expenses. Accrued expenses represent expenses incurred at the end of the reporting period but not yet paid; also called accrued liabilities. The accrued liability is shown under current liabilities in the balance sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInPremiumsReceivable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the premium receivables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInPrepaidAssets
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the prepaid assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInReceivables
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the receivables. Receivables are amounts due to be paid to the company from clients and other.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInReinsuranceRecoverableOnPaidAndUnpaidLosses
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period in the amount of benefits the ceding insurer expects to recover on insurance policies ceded to other insurance entities as of the balance sheet date for all guaranteed benefit types.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInRestrictedCash
member.summary: The net cash inflow (outflow) for the net change associated with funds that are not available for withdrawal or use (such as funds held in escrow).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInTradingAccountSecurities
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period associated with trading account assets. Trading account assets are bought and held principally for the purpose of selling them in the near term (thus held for only a short period of time). Unrealized holding gains and losses for trading securities are included in earnings.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInWorkingCapital
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the working capital. Working Capital is the amount left to the company to finance operations and expansion after current liabilities have been covered.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CumulativeEffectOfAccountingChange
member.summary: The effect on net income, net of income taxes, of a change in accounting principle reported on the income statement in the period, which occurred before previously adjustments were required.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.DeferredIncomeTax
member.summary: The component of income tax expense for the period representing the net change in the entities deferred tax assets and liabilities pertaining to continuing operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.DeferredTax
member.summary: Future tax liability or asset, resulting from temporary differences between book (accounting) value of assets and liabilities, and their tax value. This arises due to differences between financial accounting for shareholders and tax accounting.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.Depletion
member.summary: Unlike depreciation and amortization, which mainly describe the deduction of expenses due to the aging of equipment and property, depletion is the actual physical reduction of natural resources by companies. For example, coalmines, oil fields and other natural resources are depleted on company accounting statements. This reduction in the quantity of resources is meant to assist in accurately identifying the value of the asset on the balance sheet.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.Depreciation
member.summary: An expense recorded to allocate a tangible asset's cost over its useful life. Since it is a non-cash expense, it increases free cash flow while decreasing reported earnings.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.DepreciationAndAmortization
member.summary: The current period expense charged against earnings on long-lived, physical assets used in the normal conduct of business and not intended for resale to allocate or recognize the cost of assets over their useful lives; or to record the reduction in book value of an intangible asset over the benefit period of such asset.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.DepreciationAmortizationDepletion
member.summary: It is a non cash charge that represents a reduction in the value of fixed assets due to wear, age or obsolescence. This figure also includes amortization of leased property, intangibles, and goodwill, and depletion. This non-cash item is an add-back to the cash flow statement.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.EffectOfExchangeRateChanges
member.summary: The effect of exchange rate changes on cash balances held in foreign currencies.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.IncreaseDecreaseInDeposit
member.summary: The aggregate net change during the reporting period in moneys given as security, collateral, or margin deposits.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetCommonStockIssuance
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of common stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetIssuancePaymentsOfDebt
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of debt.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetLongTermDebtIssuance
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of long term debt. Long term debt includes notes payable, bonds payable, mortgage loans, convertible debt, subordinated debt and other types of long term debt.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetPreferredStockIssuance
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetShortTermDebtIssuance
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of short term debt.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetCashFromDiscontinuedOperations
member.summary: The net cash from (used in) all of the entity's discontinued operating activities, excluding those of continued operations, of the reporting entity.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetForeignCurrencyExchangeGainLoss
member.summary: The aggregate amount of realized and unrealized gain or loss resulting from changes in exchange rates between currencies. (Excludes foreign currency transactions designated as hedges of net investment in a foreign entity and inter-company foreign currency transactions that are of a long-term nature, when the entities to the transaction are consolidated, combined, or accounted for by the equity method in the reporting entity's financial statements. For certain entities, primarily banks, which are dealers in foreign exchange, foreign currency transaction gains or losses, may be disclosed as dealer gains or losses.)

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetIncome
member.summary: The profit or loss of the entity net of income taxes for the reporting period calculated and presented in the income statement in accordance with GAAP.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetIncomeFromContinuingOperations
member.summary: Revenue less expenses and taxes from the entity's ongoing operations and before income (loss) from discontinued operations, extraordinary items, impact of changes in accounting principles, minority interest, and various other reconciling adjustments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PaymentForLoans
member.summary: Payment from a bank or insurance company to the lender who lends money or property based on the agreement, along with interest, at a predetermined date in the future.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CommonStockPayments
member.summary: The cash outflow to reacquire common stock during the period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PreferredStockPayments
member.summary: The cash outflow to reacquire preferred stock during the period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.LongTermDebtPayments
member.summary: The cash outflow for debt initially having maturity due after one year or beyond the normal operating cycle, if longer.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ShortTermDebtPayments
member.summary: The cash outflow for a borrowing having initial term of repayment within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProceedsFromIssuanceOfWarrants
member.summary: The cash inflow from issuance of warrants.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProceedsFromLoans
member.summary: The cash inflow from borrowing money or property for a bank or insurance company.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProceedsFromStockOptionExercised
member.summary: The cash inflow associated with the amount received from holders exercising their stock options.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CommonStockIssuance
member.summary: The cash inflow from offering common stock, which is the additional capital contribution to the entity during the period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.LongTermDebtIssuance
member.summary: The cash inflow from a debt initially having maturity due after one year or beyond the operating cycle, if longer.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PreferredStockIssuance
member.summary: The cash inflow from offering preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ShortTermDebtIssuance
member.summary: The cash inflow from a debt initially having maturity due within one year or the normal operating cycle, if longer.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetProceedsPaymentForLoan
member.summary: The net value of proceeds or payments of loans.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProceedsPaymentInInterestBearingDepositsInBank
member.summary: The net change on interest-bearing deposits in other financial institutions for relatively short periods of time including, for example, certificates of deposits.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfEquitySecurities
member.summary: Refers to all purchases of equity securities; equity securities includes information about ownership interests or the right to acquire ownership interests in corporations and other legal entities. The ownership interest is represented by shares of common or preferred stock, convertible securities, stock rights, or stock warrants.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfFixedMaturitySecurities
member.summary: All purchases of fixed maturity securities. Fixed maturity securities represent investments in debt securities having predetermined or determinable maturity dates.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfIntangibles
member.summary: The amount of capital outlays undertaken to increase, construct or improve intangible assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfInvestment
member.summary: All purchases of investments, including both long term and short term.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfLongTermInvestments
member.summary: All purchases of long-term investments that a company intends to hold for more than a year, which may include stocks, bonds, and real estate.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfPPE
member.summary: The amount of capital outlays undertaken to increase, construct or improve capital assets. This category includes property, plant equipment, furniture, fixed assets, buildings, and improvement.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfShortTermInvestments
member.summary: All purchases of short-term investments that a company has made that will expire within one year. Examples include marketable securities, commodities, money market instruments, and options.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfTechnology
member.summary: The amount of capital outlays undertaken to increase, construct or improve technology.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PurchaseOfBusiness
member.summary: All the purchases of business including business acquisitions, investment in subsidiary; investing in affiliated companies, and join venture.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetBusinessPurchaseAndSale
member.summary: The net change between Purchases/Sales of Business.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetIntangiblesPurchaseAndSale
member.summary: The net change between Purchases/Sales of Intangibles.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetInvestmentPurchaseAndSale
member.summary: The net change between Purchases/Sales of Investments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetPPEPurchaseAndSale
member.summary: The net change between Purchases/Sales of PPE.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetTechnologyPurchaseAndSale
member.summary: The net change between Purchases/Sales of Technology.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfBusiness
member.summary: Proceeds received from selling a business including proceeds from a subsidiary, and proceeds from an affiliated company.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfIntangibles
member.summary: The amount of capital inflow from the sale of all kinds of intangible assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfInvestment
member.summary: Proceeds received from selling all kind of investments, including both long term and short term.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfLongTermInvestments
member.summary: Proceeds received from selling long-term investments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfPPE
member.summary: Proceeds from selling any fixed assets such as property, plant and equipment, which also includes retirement of equipment.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfShortTermInvestments
member.summary: Proceeds received from selling short-term investments; such as marketable securities, treasury bills; certificates of deposit, banker's acceptances, money market investments, commercial paper, Eurodollars, repurchase agreements, collateral investments, temporary investments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SaleOfTechnology
member.summary: The amount of capital inflow from the sale of technology.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SalesOfEquitySecurities
member.summary: Proceeds from the sale of all equity securities, which represent investments in common and preferred stocks and other forms of securities that provide ownership interests in a corporation.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.SalesOfFixedMaturitySecurities
member.summary: Proceeds from the sale of fixed maturity securities, which represent investments in debt securities having predetermined or determinable maturity dates.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangesInAccountReceivables
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the accounts receivables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.AmortizationOfFinancingCostsAndDiscounts
member.summary: The component of interest expense representing the non-cash expenses charged against earnings in the period to allocate debt discount and premium, and the costs to issue debt and obtain financing over the related debt instruments. This item is usually only available for bank industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.AmortizationOfSecurities
member.summary: Represents amortization of the allocation of a lump sum amount to different time periods, particularly for securities, debt, loans, and other forms of financing. Does not include amortization, amortization of capital expenditure and intangible assets.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.AssetImpairmentCharge
member.summary: The charge against earnings resulting from the aggregate write down of all assets from their carrying value to their fair value.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInDividendPayable
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the dividend payables.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInDeferredCharges
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period in the value of expenditures made during the current reporting period for benefits that will be received over a period of years. This item is usually only available for bank industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInOtherCurrentAssets
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the Other Current Assets. This category typically includes prepayments, deferred charges, and amounts (other than trade accounts) due from parents and subsidiaries.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInOtherCurrentLiabilities
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the Other Current liabilities. Other Current liabilities is a balance sheet entry used by companies to group together current liabilities that are not assigned to common liabilities such as debt obligations or accounts payable.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInOtherWorkingCapital
member.summary: The increase or decrease between periods of the other working capital.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInPrepaidReinsurancePremiums
member.summary: The net cash inflow (outflow) for the net change associated with the unexpired portion of premiums ceded on policies in force as of the balance sheet date. This item is usually only available for insurance industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInReinsuranceReceivableOnPaidLosses
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period associated with receivables currently due from reinsurers for ceded paid losses.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInReinsuranceRecoverableOnUnpaidLosses
member.summary: The net change during the reporting period associated with receivables currently due from reinsurers for ceded unpaid losses. This item is usually only available for insurance industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInUnearnedPremiums
member.summary: The change during the period in the unearned portion of premiums written, excluding the portion amortized into income. This item is usually only available for insurance industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ChangeInUnearnedPremiumsCeded
member.summary: The change during the period for unearned premiums pursuant to terms of reinsurance arrangements. This item is usually only available for insurance industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CommonStockDividendPaid
member.summary: The cash outflow from the distribution of an entity's earnings in the form of dividends to common shareholders.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.EarningsLossesFromEquityInvestments
member.summary: This item represents the entity's proportionate share for the period of the net income (loss) of its investee (such as unconsolidated subsidiaries and joint ventures) to which the equity method of accounting is applied. The amount typically reflects adjustments.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ExcessTaxBenefitFromStockBasedCompensation
member.summary: Reductions in the entity's income taxes that arise when compensation cost (from non-qualified share-based compensation) recognized on the entities tax return exceeds compensation cost from share-based compensation recognized in financial statements. This element reduces net cash provided by operating activities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ExtraordinaryItems
member.summary: Gains (losses), after tax, arising from an event or transaction that is both unusual in nature and infrequent in occurrence when considered in relation to the environment in which the entity operates. This amount should be the same as the amount disclosed on the income statement. The effect of an extraordinary event or transaction should be classified separately in the income statement if it is material in relation to income before extraordinary items or to the trend of annual earnings before extraordinary items, or is material by other appropriate criteria. Items should be considered individually and not in the aggregate in determining whether an extraordinary event or transaction is material.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.GainLossOnInvestmentSecurities
member.summary: This item represents the net total realized gain (loss) included in earnings for the period as a result of selling or holding marketable securities categorized as trading, available-for-sale, or held-to-maturity, including the unrealized holding gain or loss of held-to- maturity securities transferred to the trading security category and the cumulative unrealized gain or loss which was included in other comprehensive income (a separate component of shareholders' equity) for available-for-sale securities transferred to trading securities during the period. Additionally, this item would include any losses recognized for other than temporary impairments of the subject investments in debt and equity securities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.GainLossOnSaleOfBusiness
member.summary: The difference between the sale price or salvage price and the book value of an asset that was sold or retired during the reporting period. This element refers to the gain (loss) and not to the cash proceeds of the business. This element is a non-cash adjustment to net income when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.GainLossOnSaleOfPPE
member.summary: The difference between the sale price or salvage price and the book value of the property, plant and equipment that was sold or retired during the reporting period. Includes the amount received from selling any fixed assets such as property, plant and equipment. Usually this section also includes any retirement of equipment. Such as Sale of business segments; Sale of credit and receivables; Property disposition; Proceeds from sale or disposition of business or investment; Decrease in excess of purchase price over acquired net assets; Abandoned project (expenditures) credit; Allowances for other funds during construction.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.InterestCreditedOnPolicyholderDeposits
member.summary: An expense reported in the income statement and needs to be removed from net income to arrive at cash provided by (used in) operations to the extent that such interest has not been paid. This item is usually only available for insurance industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.CashFromDiscontinuedOperatingActivities
member.summary: The net cash from (used in) all of the entity's discontinued operating activities, excluding those of continued operations, of the reporting entity.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.OperatingGainsLosses
member.summary: The gain or loss from the entity's ongoing operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetOtherFinancingCharges
member.summary: Miscellaneous charges incurred due to Financing activities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.NetOtherInvestingChanges
member.summary: Miscellaneous charges incurred due to Investing activities.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.OtherNonCashItems
member.summary: Items which adjusted back from net income but without real cash outflow or inflow.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PensionAndEmployeeBenefitExpense
member.summary: The amount of pension and other (such as medical, dental and life insurance) postretirement benefit costs recognized during the period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.PreferredStockDividendPaid
member.summary: Pay for the amount of dividends declared or paid in the period to preferred shareholders or the amount for which the obligation to pay them dividends rose in the period.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProceedsPaymentFederalFundsSoldAndSecuritiesPurchasedUnderAgreementToResell
member.summary: The aggregate amount change of (1) the lending of excess federal funds to another commercial bank requiring such for its legal reserve requirements and (2) securities purchased under agreements to resell. This item is usually only available for bank industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.ProvisionForLoanLeaseAndOtherLosses
member.summary: The sum of the periodic provision charged to earnings, based on an assessment of uncollectible from the counterparty on account of loan, lease or other credit losses, to reduce these accounts to the amount that approximates their net realizable value. This item is usually only available for bank industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.RealizedGainLossOnSaleOfLoansAndLease
member.summary: The gains and losses included in earnings that represent the difference between the sale price and the carrying value of loans and leases that were sold during the reporting period. This element refers to the gain (loss) and not to the cash proceeds of the sales. This element is a non-cash adjustment to net income when calculating net cash generated by operating activities using the indirect method. This item is usually only available for bank industry.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CashFlowStatement.StockBasedCompensation

member.name: T:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference
member.summary: Definition of the CompanyReference class

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.CompanyId
member.summary: 10-digit unique and unchanging Morningstar identifier assigned to every company.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.ShortName
member.summary: 25-character max abbreviated name of the firm. In most cases, the short name will simply be the Legal Name less the "Corporation", "Corp.", "Inc.", "Incorporated", etc...

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.StandardName
member.summary: The English translation of the foreign legal name if/when applicable.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.LegalName
member.summary: The full name of the registrant as specified in its charter, and most often found on the front cover of the 10K/10Q/20F filing.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.CountryId
member.summary: 3 Character ISO code of the country where the firm is domiciled. See separate reference document for Country Mappings.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.CIK
member.summary: The Central Index Key; a corporate identifier assigned by the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.CompanyStatus
member.summary: At the Company level; each company is assigned to 1 of 3 possible status classifications; (U) Public, (V) Private, or (O) Obsolete: - Public-Firm is operating and currently has at least one common share class that is currently trading on a public exchange. - Private-Firm is operating but does not have any common share classes currently trading on a public exchange. - Obsolete-Firm is no longer operating because it closed its business, or was acquired.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.FiscalYearEnd
member.summary: The Month of the company's latest fiscal year.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.IndustryTemplateCode
member.summary: This indicator will denote which one of the six industry data collection templates applies to the company. Each industry data collection template includes data elements that are commonly reported by companies in that industry. N=Normal (Manufacturing), M=Mining, U=Utility, T=Transportation, B=Bank, I=Insurance

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.PrimaryShareClassID
member.summary: The 10-digit unique and unchanging Morningstar identifier assigned to the Primary Share class of a company. The primary share of a company is defined as the first share that was traded publicly and is still actively trading. If this share is no longer trading, the primary share will be the share with the highest volume.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.PrimarySymbol
member.summary: The symbol of the Primary Share of the company, composed of an arrangement of characters (often letters) representing a particular security listed on an exchange or otherwise traded publicly. The primary share of a company is defined as the first share that was traded publicly and is still actively trading. If this share is no longer trading, the primary share will be the share with the highest volume. Note: Morningstar's multi-share class symbols will often contain a "period" within the symbol; e.g. BRK.B for Berkshire Hathaway Class B.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.PrimaryExchangeID
member.summary: The Id representing the stock exchange of the Primary Share of the company. See separate reference document for Exchange Mappings. The primary share of a company is defined as the first share that was traded publicly with and is still actively trading. If this share is no longer trading, the primary share will be the share with the highest volume.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.BusinessCountryID
member.summary: In some cases, different from the country of domicile (CountryId; DataID 5). This element is a three (3) Character ISO code of the business country of the security. It is determined by a few factors, including:

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.LegalNameLanguageCode
member.summary: The language code for the foreign legal name if/when applicable. Related to DataID 4 (LegalName).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.Auditor
member.summary: The legal (registered) name of the company's current auditor. Distinct from DataID 28000 Period Auditor that identifies the Auditor related to that period's financial statements.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.AuditorLanguageCode
member.summary: The ISO code denoting the language text for Auditor's name and contact information.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.Advisor
member.summary: The legal (registered) name of the current legal Advisor of the company.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.AdvisorLanguageCode
member.summary: The ISO code denoting the language text for Advisor's name and contact information.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.IsLimitedPartnership
member.summary: Indicator to denote if the company is a limited partnership, which is a form of business structure comprised of a general partner and limited partners. 1 denotes it is a LP; otherwise 0.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.IsREIT
member.summary: Indicator to denote if the company is a real estate investment trust (REIT). 1 denotes it is a REIT; otherwise 0.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.PrimaryMIC
member.summary: The MIC (market identifier code) of the PrimarySymbol of the company. See Data Appendix A for the relevant MIC to exchange name mapping.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.ReportStyle
member.summary: This refers to the financial template used to collect the company's financial statements. There are two report styles representing two different financial template structures. Report style "1" is most commonly used by US and Canadian companies, and Report style "3" is most commonly used by the rest of the universe. Contact your client manager for access to the respective templates.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.CompanyReference.YearofEstablishment
member.summary: The year a company was founded.

member.name: T:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios
member.summary: Definition of the EarningRatios class

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios.DilutedEPSGrowth
member.summary: The growth in the company's diluted earnings per share (EPS) on a percentage basis. Morningstar calculates the annualized growth percentage based on the underlying diluted EPS reported in the Income Statement within the company filings or reports.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios.DilutedContEPSGrowth
member.summary: The growth in the company's diluted EPS from continuing operations on a percentage basis. Morningstar calculates the annualized growth percentage based on the underlying diluted EPS from continuing operations reported in the Income Statement within the company filings or reports.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios.DPSGrowth
member.summary: The growth in the company's dividends per share (DPS) on a percentage basis. Morningstar calculates the annualized growth percentage based on the underlying DPS from its dividend database. Morningstar collects its DPS from company filings and reports, as well as from third party sources.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios.EquityPerShareGrowth
member.summary: The growth in the company's book value per share on a percentage basis. Morningstar calculates the annualized growth percentage based on the underlying equity and end of period shares outstanding reported in the company filings or reports.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningRatios.RegressionGrowthofDividends5Years
member.summary: The five-year growth rate of dividends per share, calculated using regression analysis.

member.name: T:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports
member.summary: Definition of the EarningReports class

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.PeriodEndingDate
member.summary: The exact date that is given in the financial statements for each quarter's end.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.FileDate
member.summary: Specific date on which a company released its filing to the public.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.AccessionNumber
member.summary: The accession number is a unique number that EDGAR assigns to each submission as the submission is received.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.FormType
member.summary: The type of filing of the report: for instance, 10-K (annual report) or 10-Q (quarterly report).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicContinuousOperations
member.summary: Basic EPS from Continuing Operations is the earnings from continuing operations reported by the company divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicDiscontinuousOperations
member.summary: Basic EPS from Discontinued Operations is the earnings from discontinued operations reported by the company divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding. This only includes gain or loss from discontinued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicExtraordinary
member.summary: Basic EPS from the Extraordinary Gains/Losses is the earnings attributable to the gains or losses (during the reporting period) from extraordinary items divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicAccountingChange
member.summary: Basic EPS from the Cumulative Effect of Accounting Change is the earnings attributable to the accounting change (during the reporting period) divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicEPS
member.summary: Basic EPS is the bottom line net income divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedContinuousOperations
member.summary: Diluted EPS from Continuing Operations is the earnings from continuing operations divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, and convertible preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedDiscontinuousOperations
member.summary: Diluted EPS from Discontinued Operations is the earnings from discontinued operations divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, and convertible preferred stock. This only includes gain or loss from discontinued operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedExtraordinary
member.summary: Diluted EPS from Extraordinary Gain/Losses is the gain or loss from extraordinary items divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, and convertible preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedAccountingChange
member.summary: Diluted EPS from Cumulative Effect Accounting Changes is the earnings from accounting changes (in the reporting period) divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, and convertible preferred stock.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedEPS
member.summary: Diluted EPS is the bottom line net income divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, and convertible preferred stock. This value will be derived when not reported for the fourth quarter and will be less than or equal to Basic EPS.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicAverageShares
member.summary: The shares outstanding used to calculate Basic EPS, which is the weighted average common share outstanding through the whole accounting period. Note: If Basic Average Shares are not presented by the firm in the Income Statement, this data point will be null.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedAverageShares
member.summary: The shares outstanding used to calculate the diluted EPS, assuming the conversion of all convertible securities and the exercise of warrants or stock options. It is the weighted average diluted share outstanding through the whole accounting period. Note: If Diluted Average Shares are not presented by the firm in the Income Statement and Basic Average Shares are presented, Diluted Average Shares will equal Basic Average Shares. However, if neither value is presented by the firm, Diluted Average Shares will be null.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DividendPerShare
member.summary: The amount of dividend that a stockholder will receive for each share of stock held. It can be calculated by taking the total amount of dividends paid and dividing it by the total shares outstanding. Dividend per share = total dividend payment/total number of outstanding shares

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.BasicEPSOtherGainsLosses
member.summary: Basic EPS from the Other Gains/Losses is the earnings attributable to the other gains/losses (during the reporting period) divided by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.ContinuingAndDiscontinuedBasicEPS
member.summary: Basic EPS from Continuing Operations plus Basic EPS from Discontinued Operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.TaxLossCarryforwardBasicEPS
member.summary: The earnings attributable to the tax loss carry forward (during the reporting period).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.DilutedEPSOtherGainsLosses
member.summary: The earnings from gains and losses (in the reporting period) divided by the common shares outstanding adjusted for the assumed conversion of all potentially dilutive securities. Securities having a dilutive effect may include convertible debentures, warrants, options, convertible preferred stock, etc.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.ContinuingAndDiscontinuedDilutedEPS
member.summary: Diluted EPS from Continuing Operations plus Diluted EPS from Discontinued Operations.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.TaxLossCarryforwardDilutedEPS
member.summary: The earnings from any tax loss carry forward (in the reporting period).

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.NormalizedBasicEPS
member.summary: The basic normalized earnings per share. Normalized EPS removes onetime and unusual items from EPS, to provide investors with a more accurate measure of the company's true earnings. Normalized Earnings / Basic Weighted Average Shares Outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.NormalizedDilutedEPS
member.summary: The diluted normalized earnings per share. Normalized EPS removes onetime and unusual items from EPS, to provide investors with a more accurate measure of the company's true earnings. Normalized Earnings / Diluted Weighted Average Shares Outstanding.

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.EarningReports.TotalDividendPerShare
member.summary: Total Dividend Per Share is cash dividends and special cash dividends paid per share over a certain period of time

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.FinancialStatements.InventoryValuationMethod
member.summary: Which method of inventory valuation was used - LIFO, FIFO, Average, Standard costs, Net realizable value, Others, LIFO and FIFO, FIFO and Average, FIFO and other, LIFO and Average, LIFO and other, Average and other, 3 or more methods, None

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.FinancialStatements.NumberOfShareHolders
member.summary: The number of shareholders on record

member.name: P:QuantConnect.Data.Fundamental.FinancialStatements.TotalRiskBasedCapital
member.summary: The sum of Tier 1 and Tier 2 Capital. Tier 1 capital consists of common shareholders equity, perpetual preferred shareholders equity with non-cumulative dividends, retained earnings, and minority interests in the equity accounts of consolidated subsidiaries. Tier 2 capital consists of subordinated debt, intermediate-term preferred stock, cumulative and long-term preferred stock, and a portion of a banks allowance for loan and lease losses.
